This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on autonomous mobile manipulation tasks. It also involves computer vision techniques such as object detection and 6D pose estimation, which suggests it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of CNNs and generative sampling methods suggests it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves generating 3D object poses.
